                                                                                               NIST SP 800-53A REV. 5                ASSESSING SECURITY AND PRIVACY CONTROLS IN INFORMATION SYSTEMS AND ORGANIZATIONS
                                                                                               _________________________________________________________________________________________________


                                                                                               Figure 4 provides an example of an assessment procedure for a control, MP-07, that includes
                                                                                               assignment operations and a selection operation. Selection operations include a list of potential
                                                                                               parameter values that the organization chooses from and instructions to select one or more
                                                                                               parameters. The list of parameter values is identified using braces { }, with each potential
                                                                                               parameter value separated with a semicolon. When the ODP for a selection operation is
                                                                                               referenced in a subsequent determination statement, the ODP unique identifier and phrase
                                                                                               “SELECTED PARAMETER VALUE(S)” is surrounded by < >.

